The paper proposes a new algorithm for training Takagi-Sugeno-Kang (TSK) fuzzy systems for regression problems, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm involves regularization, drop rule, and AdaBound, which are optimization techniques commonly used in neural networks, suggesting a possible connection to neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). The paper also proposes a rule pruning algorithm, which involves selecting a subset of rules from the TSK fuzzy system, a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and data mining (cs.DM).
